Five disciples, each a grand master in a particular style of kung fu, are banded together by a wise old drunken monk.
He leads the band of fighters on a mission to catch a group of evil martial arts experts and white-haired wizards from China and Tibet in the ultimate martial arts fight to the finish.
This is without a doubt, the greatest kung fu movie ever! The action is fantastic, and the training sequences are long and quite inventive. This movie has a great cast of likeable heroes, and impressive villains that all fight like kung fu superheroes.
 The master is the greatest character in movie history, and is not someone you would want to mess with. This is one of the first kung fu flicks i saw, and it still is my favorite. Everyone needs to see this movie at least once, so dont let the dull box discourage you, pick up this lost gem today!!!
